Any opinion? You seem like a nice man and pretty funny. Also, you're a good defender amigo ;v

Which ocn tm do you like most? Why? Personally I think I would have loved hoc, because I love dtc and the streams were amazing, but unfortunately I only started competitive in aoa. TLOA was my favorite by a lot. Every other tournamnet I either hardly got to play (bttc and soc), it was hosted on my birthday so i didnt play (aoa) or was out of town (rogue gamemodes), or had massive internet problems (kfc). Plus, I loved almost every map in the pool. It also helped that I played very well that tournament, for example when, on ssb i completed both of eclipses monuments 100% in two minutes, and went on to leak their core later.

Do you miss me when i leave pb tryout? Yeah. You were cool, plus I was worried pb was only gonna have 1 defender because if i recall correctly, sinnes and matt hadnt joined yet

replies.body:
The Bulldog is a medium-sized breed of dog commonly referred to as the English Bulldog or British Bulldog. Other Bulldog breeds include the American Bulldog, Old English Bulldog (now extinct), Leavitt Bulldog, Olde English Bulldogge, and the French Bulldog. The Bulldog is a muscular, hefty dog with a wrinkled face and a distinctive pushed-in nose.[4] The American Kennel Club (AKC), The Kennel Club (UK), and the United Kennel Club (UKC) oversee breeding records. Bulldogs were the fourth most popular purebreed in the US in 2015 according to the American Kennel Club.[5]

The Bulldog has a longstanding association with British culture, with the BBC stating: "to many the Bulldog is a national icon, symbolising pluck and determination."[6]During World War II the Bulldog was often likened to Prime Minister Winston Churchill and his defiance of Nazi Germany.
